<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="84" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,223,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is an adjective composed of Annapurna (mountain) and Latin suffix - 
<emphasis box="[1380,1436,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">ensis</emphasis>
(meaning, ‘of’ or ‘from’), indicating the place of the origin.
</paragraph>
